<br />
You mean after installing Textual Confirmation?
<br />

<br />
Textual Confirmation uses the standard phpBB functionality to send e-mails. Therefore, if TC mail fails, then most likely any mail from phpBB fails. Please check.
<br />

<br />
If phpBB mail works, but TC mail doesn't, pleae try following and report results. In file &quot;functions_tc.php&quot;, find
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">$from = &quot;$from &lt;&quot; . $board_config&#91;'board_email'&#93; . '&gt;';</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
and change it to
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">$from = $board_config&#91;'board_email'&#93;;</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Oleg Parashchenko, bbAntiSpam
<br />
Do you love our tools? <a href="https://www.plimus.com/jsp/buynow.jsp?contractId=1671485" target="_blank" class="postlink">Please sponsor</a> further development!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
